      "message": "Unless there\u0027s a really strong rationale for it, we should avoid using pair\u003c\u003e where we could create a struct with named elements. i.e. there doesn\u0027t seem to be any reason not to have:\n\n  struct LoadedModule { \n    std::shared_ptr\u003cSymbolTable\u003e fSymbolTable;\n    std::vector\u003cstd::unique_ptr\u003cProgramElement\u003e\u003e fProgramElements; \n  }\n\nhttps://google.github.io/styleguide/cppguide.html#Structs_vs._Tuples\n\nNote that capture syntax (`auto [symbols, elements] \u003d `) should still work even on a struct, if you want to keep that, but it should be less necessary overall.",
